believe that the scores were horrible and that I would need to curve it.
The thing I finally got about writing exams is that they are not meant for
everyone to pass them.  Sometimes, there are hard questions.  My aforementioned
TA seemed to complain about some of the tough problems on the exam, but it
turned out that there were people who got them correct.  Because I have been
afraid of not being able to curve the class because the grades are so high, I
see the value in having a test where different levels of people score
differently on them.

